mood_emotions.response: The image of the fighter jet in mid-flight conveys a mood of intensity and readiness, evoking feelings of power, precision, and perhaps a sense of awe. The overall tone is neutral to slightly positive, as the jet appears to be in a controlled and purposeful state, suggesting capability and preparedness. The sleek design and aerodynamic features of the aircraft contribute to a sense of sophistication and advanced technology. The clear sky in the background enhances the feeling of freedom and vastness, while the visible landing gear and the pilot in the cockpit add a human element, emphasizing the blend of machine and human skill. The image does not evoke negative emotions; instead, it highlights the marvel of modern engineering and the dedication of those who operate such machinery.

structured_inventory.prompt_text:
Analyze this image and create a JSON object documenting all visible items. Structure the output with these exact three levels:
Level 1 (Categories): Use only these four keys: 'human', 'animal', 'man-made', 'natural'
Level 2 (Item names): Specific names of detected items (e.g., 'person', 'dog', 'car', 'tree')
Level 3 (Attributes): Use ONLY these keys for each item:
  • count: number of instances (integer)
  • location: position in image (use terms like: left/center/right, top/middle/bottom, foreground/background)
  • color: main color(s) if applicable (array of strings)
  • size: relative size (small/medium/large)
  • description: any other relevant details that don't fit above categories (string)
Output valid JSON only. Include only categories that contain detected items. If an attribute doesn't apply to an item (e.g., color for sky), omit that key rather than using null. The 'description' field should capture important characteristics like actions, states, or specific features not covered by other keys.

aircraft.description: A military jet in flight, with visible landing gear and cockpit.

missile.description: A missile attached underneath the aircraft.

pilot.description: A person visible in the cockpit of the aircraft.
